{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":528,"text":"So in 1885, Karl Benz\ninvented the automobile."},{"time":4707,"text":"Later that year, he took it out\nfor the first public test drive,"},{"time":8469,"text":"and -- true story --\ncrashed into a wall."},{"time":12184,"text":"For the last 130 years,"},{"time":14227,"text":"we've been working around that least\nreliable part of the car, the driver."},{"time":18546,"text":"We've made the car stronger."},{"time":20200,"text":"We've added seat belts,\nwe've added air bags,"},{"time":22748,"text":"and in the last decade, we've actually\nstarted trying to make the car smarter"},{"time":26719,"text":"to fix that bug, the driver."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29657,"text":"Now, today I'm going to talk to you\na little bit about the difference"},{"time":32918,"text":"between patching around the problem\nwith driver assistance systems"},{"time":36726,"text":"and actually having fully\nself-driving cars"},{"time":39290,"text":"and what they can do for the world."},{"time":41170,"text":"I'm also going to talk to you\na little bit about our car"},{"time":44165,"text":"and allow you to see how it sees the world\nand how it reacts and what it does,"},{"time":48164,"text":"but first I'm going to talk\na little bit about the problem."},{"time":51651,"text":"And it's a big problem:"},{"time":53299,"text":"1.2 million people are killed\non the world's roads every year."},{"time":56388,"text":"In America alone, 33,000 people\nare killed each year."},{"time":60172,"text":"To put that in perspective,"},{"time":62200,"text":"that's the same as a 737\nfalling out of the sky every working day."},{"time":67342,"text":"It's kind of unbelievable."},{"time":69548,"text":"Cars are sold to us like this,"},{"time":71846,"text":"but really, this is what driving's like."},{"time":74563,"text":"Right? It's not sunny, it's rainy,"},{"time":76722,"text":"and you want to do anything\nother than drive."},{"time":79210,"text":"And the reason why is this:"},{"time":80832,"text":"Traffic is getting worse."},{"time":82690,"text":"In America, between 1990 and 2010,"},{"time":86196,"text":"the vehicle miles traveled\nincreased by 38 percent."},{"time":90213,"text":"We grew by six percent of roads,"},{"time":92962,"text":"so it's not in your brains."},{"time":94564,"text":"Traffic really is substantially worse\nthan it was not very long ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98840,"text":"And all of this has a very human cost."},{"time":101529,"text":"So if you take the average commute time\nin America, which is about 50 minutes,"},{"time":105477,"text":"you multiply that by the 120 million\nworkers we have,"},{"time":109126,"text":"that turns out to be\nabout six billion minutes"},{"time":111351,"text":"wasted in commuting every day."},{"time":113377,"text":"Now, that's a big number,\nso let's put it in perspective."},{"time":116204,"text":"You take that six billion minutes"},{"time":117978,"text":"and you divide it by the average\nlife expectancy of a person,"},{"time":121762,"text":"that turns out to be 162 lifetimes"},{"time":124897,"text":"spent every day, wasted,"},{"time":127822,"text":"just getting from A to B."},{"time":129866,"text":"It's unbelievable."},{"time":131596,"text":"And then, there are those of us\nwho don't have the privilege"},{"time":134440,"text":"of sitting in traffic."},{"time":136112,"text":"So this is Steve."},{"time":137690,"text":"He's an incredibly capable guy,"},{"time":139455,"text":"but he just happens to be blind,"},{"time":141971,"text":"and that means instead of a 30-minute\ndrive to work in the morning,"},{"time":145188,"text":"it's a two-hour ordeal\nof piecing together bits of public transit"},{"time":149167,"text":"or asking friends and family for a ride."},{"time":151552,"text":"He doesn't have that same freedom\nthat you and I have to get around."},{"time":155221,"text":"We should do something about that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":157891,"text":"Now, conventional wisdom would say"},{"time":159648,"text":"that we'll just take\nthese driver assistance systems"},{"time":162140,"text":"and we'll kind of push them\nand incrementally improve them,"},{"time":165890,"text":"and over time, they'll turn\ninto self-driving cars."},{"time":168432,"text":"Well, I'm here to tell you\nthat's like me saying"},{"time":170841,"text":"that if I work really hard at jumping,\none day I'll be able to fly."},{"time":174898,"text":"We actually need to do\nsomething a little different."},{"time":177626,"text":"And so I'm going to talk to you\nabout three different ways"},{"time":180337,"text":"that self-driving systems are different\nthan driver assistance systems."},{"time":183683,"text":"And I'm going to start\nwith some of our own experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186334,"text":"So back in 2013,"},{"time":188587,"text":"we had the first test\nof a self-driving car"},{"time":191250,"text":"where we let regular people use it."},{"time":193277,"text":"Well, almost regular --\nthey were 100 Googlers,"},{"time":195479,"text":"but they weren't working on the project."},{"time":197482,"text":"And we gave them the car and we allowed\nthem to use it in their daily lives."},{"time":201103,"text":"But unlike a real self-driving car,\nthis one had a big asterisk with it:"},{"time":204822,"text":"They had to pay attention,"},{"time":206326,"text":"because this was an experimental vehicle."},{"time":208959,"text":"We tested it a lot,\nbut it could still fail."},{"time":212484,"text":"And so we gave them two hours of training,"},{"time":214543,"text":"we put them in the car,\nwe let them use it,"},{"time":216635,"text":"and what we heard back\nwas something awesome,"},{"time":218762,"text":"as someone trying\nto bring a product into the world."},{"time":221286,"text":"Every one of them told us they loved it."},{"time":223211,"text":"In fact, we had a Porsche driver\nwho came in and told us on the first day,"},{"time":226777,"text":"\"This is completely stupid.\nWhat are we thinking?\""},{"time":229850,"text":"But at the end of it, he said,\n\"Not only should I have it,"},{"time":232690,"text":"everyone else should have it,\nbecause people are terrible drivers.\""},{"time":237135,"text":"So this was music to our ears,"},{"time":238870,"text":"but then we started to look at what\nthe people inside the car were doing,"},{"time":242673,"text":"and this was eye-opening."},{"time":244252,"text":"Now, my favorite story is this gentleman"},{"time":246690,"text":"who looks down at his phone\nand realizes the battery is low,"},{"time":250519,"text":"so he turns around like this in the car\nand digs around in his backpack,"},{"time":255067,"text":"pulls out his laptop,"},{"time":257220,"text":"puts it on the seat,"},{"time":258787,"text":"goes in the back again,"},{"time":260551,"text":"digs around, pulls out\nthe charging cable for his phone,"},{"time":263918,"text":"futzes around, puts it into the laptop,\nputs it on the phone."},{"time":267285,"text":"Sure enough, the phone is charging."},{"time":269328,"text":"All the time he's been doing\n65 miles per hour down the freeway."},{"time":273322,"text":"Right? Unbelievable."},{"time":275806,"text":"So we thought about this and we said,\nit's kind of obvious, right?"},{"time":278927,"text":"The better the technology gets,"},{"time":281190,"text":"the less reliable\nthe driver is going to get."},{"time":283311,"text":"So by just making the cars\nincrementally smarter,"},{"time":285707,"text":"we're probably not going to see\nthe wins we really need."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288609,"text":"Let me talk about something\na little technical for a moment here."},{"time":292510,"text":"So we're looking at this graph,\nand along the bottom"},{"time":294948,"text":"is how often does the car\napply the brakes when it shouldn't."},{"time":297999,"text":"You can ignore most of that axis,"},{"time":299620,"text":"because if you're driving around town,\nand the car starts stopping randomly,"},{"time":303339,"text":"you're never going to buy that car."},{"time":305040,"text":"And the vertical axis is how often\nthe car is going to apply the brakes"},{"time":308415,"text":"when it's supposed to\nto help you avoid an accident."},{"time":311464,"text":"Now, if we look at\nthe bottom left corner here,"},{"time":313685,"text":"this is your classic car."},{"time":315530,"text":"It doesn't apply the brakes for you,\nit doesn't do anything goofy,"},{"time":318663,"text":"but it also doesn't get you\nout of an accident."},{"time":321442,"text":"Now, if we want to bring\na driver assistance system into a car,"},{"time":324460,"text":"say with collision mitigation braking,"},{"time":326288,"text":"we're going to put some package\nof technology on there,"},{"time":328900,"text":"and that's this curve, and it's going\nto have some operating properties,"},{"time":332318,"text":"but it's never going to avoid\nall of the accidents,"},{"time":334808,"text":"because it doesn't have that capability."},{"time":336867,"text":"But we'll pick some place\nalong the curve here,"},{"time":339116,"text":"and maybe it avoids half of accidents\nthat the human driver misses,"},{"time":342370,"text":"and that's amazing, right?"},{"time":343667,"text":"We just reduced accidents on our roads\nby a factor of two."},{"time":346394,"text":"There are now 17,000 less people\ndying every year in America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350381,"text":"But if we want a self-driving car,"},{"time":352401,"text":"we need a technology curve\nthat looks like this."},{"time":354708,"text":"We're going to have to put\nmore sensors in the vehicle,"},{"time":357307,"text":"and we'll pick some\noperating point up here"},{"time":359328,"text":"where it basically never\ngets into a crash."},{"time":361347,"text":"They'll happen, but very low frequency."},{"time":363790,"text":"Now you and I could look at this\nand we could argue"},{"time":366251,"text":"about whether it's incremental, and\nI could say something like \"80-20 rule,\""},{"time":369856,"text":"and it's really hard to move up\nto that new curve."},{"time":372424,"text":"But let's look at it\nfrom a different direction for a moment."},{"time":375358,"text":"So let's look at how often\nthe technology has to do the right thing."},{"time":378870,"text":"And so this green dot up here\nis a driver assistance system."},{"time":382376,"text":"It turns out that human drivers"},{"time":384861,"text":"make mistakes that lead\nto traffic accidents"},{"time":387508,"text":"about once every 100,000 miles in America."},{"time":390680,"text":"In contrast, a self-driving system\nis probably making decisions"},{"time":393847,"text":"about 10 times per second,"},{"time":397510,"text":"so order of magnitude,"},{"time":398932,"text":"that's about 1,000 times per mile."},{"time":401764,"text":"So if you compare the distance\nbetween these two,"},{"time":404249,"text":"it's about 10 to the eighth, right?"},{"time":406849,"text":"Eight orders of magnitude."},{"time":408614,"text":"That's like comparing how fast I run"},{"time":411423,"text":"to the speed of light."},{"time":413629,"text":"It doesn't matter how hard I train,\nI'm never actually going to get there."},{"time":417414,"text":"So there's a pretty big gap there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419852,"text":"And then finally, there's how\nthe system can handle uncertainty."},{"time":423581,"text":"So this pedestrian here might be\nstepping into the road, might not be."},{"time":426904,"text":"I can't tell,\nnor can any of our algorithms,"},{"time":430310,"text":"but in the case of\na driver assistance system,"},{"time":432594,"text":"that means it can't take action,\nbecause again,"},{"time":435400,"text":"if it presses the brakes unexpectedly,\nthat's completely unacceptable."},{"time":438739,"text":"Whereas a self-driving system\ncan look at that pedestrian and say,"},{"time":441872,"text":"I don't know what they're about to do,"},{"time":443762,"text":"slow down, take a better look,\nand then react appropriately after that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447524,"text":"So it can be much safer than\na driver assistance system can ever be."},{"time":451226,"text":"So that's enough about\nthe differences between the two."},{"time":453956,"text":"Let's spend some time talking about\nhow the car sees the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":457440,"text":"So this is our vehicle."},{"time":458692,"text":"It starts by understanding\nwhere it is in the world,"},{"time":461130,"text":"by taking a map and its sensor data\nand aligning the two,"},{"time":463917,"text":"and then we layer on top of that\nwhat it sees in the moment."},{"time":466865,"text":"So here, all the purple boxes you can see\nare other vehicles on the road,"},{"time":470520,"text":"and the red thing on the side\nover there is a cyclist,"},{"time":473048,"text":"and up in the distance,\nif you look really closely,"},{"time":475450,"text":"you can see some cones."},{"time":477244,"text":"Then we know where the car\nis in the moment,"},{"time":480017,"text":"but we have to do better than that:\nwe have to predict what's going to happen."},{"time":483850,"text":"So here the pickup truck in top right\nis about to make a left lane change"},{"time":487338,"text":"because the road in front of it is closed,"},{"time":489561,"text":"so it needs to get out of the way."},{"time":491292,"text":"Knowing that one pickup truck is great,"},{"time":493155,"text":"but we really need to know\nwhat everybody's thinking,"},{"time":495634,"text":"so it becomes quite a complicated problem."},{"time":498141,"text":"And then given that, we can figure out\nhow the car should respond in the moment,"},{"time":502890,"text":"so what trajectory it should follow, how\nquickly it should slow down or speed up."},{"time":506756,"text":"And then that all turns into\njust following a path:"},{"time":509821,"text":"turning the steering wheel left or right,\npressing the brake or gas."},{"time":513018,"text":"It's really just two numbers\nat the end of the day."},{"time":515482,"text":"So how hard can it really be?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":518433,"text":"Back when we started in 2009,"},{"time":520385,"text":"this is what our system looked like."},{"time":522183,"text":"So you can see our car in the middle\nand the other boxes on the road,"},{"time":525574,"text":"driving down the highway."},{"time":526845,"text":"The car needs to understand where it is\nand roughly where the other vehicles are."},{"time":530663,"text":"It's really a geometric\nunderstanding of the world."},{"time":533092,"text":"Once we started driving\non neighborhood and city streets,"},{"time":536040,"text":"the problem becomes a whole\nnew level of difficulty."},{"time":538485,"text":"You see pedestrians crossing in front\nof us, cars crossing in front of us,"},{"time":541979,"text":"going every which way,"},{"time":543790,"text":"the traffic lights, crosswalks."},{"time":545317,"text":"It's an incredibly complicated\nproblem by comparison."},{"time":548114,"text":"And then once you have\nthat problem solved,"},{"time":550217,"text":"the vehicle has to be able\nto deal with construction."},{"time":552729,"text":"So here are the cones on the left\nforcing it to drive to the right,"},{"time":555880,"text":"but not just construction\nin isolation, of course."},{"time":558282,"text":"It has to deal with other people moving\nthrough that construction zone as well."},{"time":562005,"text":"And of course, if anyone's\nbreaking the rules, the police are there"},{"time":565268,"text":"and the car has to understand that\nthat flashing light on the top of the car"},{"time":568890,"text":"means that it's not just a car,\nit's actually a police officer."},{"time":571995,"text":"Similarly, the orange box\non the side here,"},{"time":574027,"text":"it's a school bus,"},{"time":575136,"text":"and we have to treat that\ndifferently as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578576,"text":"When we're out on the road,\nother people have expectations:"},{"time":581369,"text":"So, when a cyclist puts up their arm,"},{"time":583149,"text":"it means they're expecting the car\nto yield to them and make room for them"},{"time":586667,"text":"to make a lane change."},{"time":589030,"text":"And when a police officer\nstood in the road,"},{"time":591203,"text":"our vehicle should understand\nthat this means stop,"},{"time":593943,"text":"and when they signal to go,\nwe should continue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597449,"text":"Now, the way we accomplish this\nis by sharing data between the vehicles."},{"time":601210,"text":"The first, most crude model of this"},{"time":602906,"text":"is when one vehicle\nsees a construction zone,"},{"time":605019,"text":"having another know about it\nso it can be in the correct lane"},{"time":608081,"text":"to avoid some of the difficulty."},{"time":609651,"text":"But we actually have a much\ndeeper understanding of this."},{"time":612315,"text":"We could take all of the data\nthat the cars have seen over time,"},{"time":615324,"text":"the hundreds of thousands\nof pedestrians, cyclists,"},{"time":617700,"text":"and vehicles that have been out there"},{"time":619487,"text":"and understand what they look like"},{"time":621182,"text":"and use that to infer\nwhat other vehicles should look like"},{"time":624013,"text":"and other pedestrians should look like."},{"time":625939,"text":"And then, even more importantly,\nwe could take from that a model"},{"time":628960,"text":"of how we expect them\nto move through the world."},{"time":631290,"text":"So here the yellow box is a pedestrian\ncrossing in front of us."},{"time":634253,"text":"Here the blue box is a cyclist\nand we anticipate"},{"time":636503,"text":"that they're going to nudge out\nand around the car to the right."},{"time":640115,"text":"Here there's a cyclist\ncoming down the road"},{"time":642207,"text":"and we know they're going to continue\nto drive down the shape of the road."},{"time":645693,"text":"Here somebody makes a right turn,"},{"time":647560,"text":"and in a moment here, somebody's\ngoing to make a U-turn in front of us,"},{"time":650920,"text":"and we can anticipate that behavior\nand respond safely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653534,"text":"Now, that's all well and good\nfor things that we've seen,"},{"time":656262,"text":"but of course, you encounter\nlots of things that you haven't"},{"time":659127,"text":"seen in the world before."},{"time":660358,"text":"And so just a couple of months ago,"},{"time":662099,"text":"our vehicles were driving\nthrough Mountain View,"},{"time":664334,"text":"and this is what we encountered."},{"time":665978,"text":"This is a woman in an electric wheelchair"},{"time":668060,"text":"chasing a duck in circles on the road.\n(Laughter)"},{"time":670677,"text":"Now it turns out, there is nowhere\nin the DMV handbook"},{"time":673788,"text":"that tells you how to deal with that,"},{"time":676033,"text":"but our vehicles were able\nto encounter that,"},{"time":678176,"text":"slow down, and drive safely."},{"time":680431,"text":"Now, we don't have to deal\nwith just ducks."},{"time":682472,"text":"Watch this bird fly across in front of us.\nThe car reacts to that."},{"time":686180,"text":"Here we're dealing with a cyclist"},{"time":687795,"text":"that you would never expect to see\nanywhere other than Mountain View."},{"time":691085,"text":"And of course, we have\nto deal with drivers,"},{"time":693153,"text":"even the very small ones."},{"time":696868,"text":"Watch to the right as someone\njumps out of this truck at us."},{"time":702460,"text":"And now, watch the left as the car\nwith the green box decides"},{"time":705389,"text":"he needs to make a right turn\nat the last possible moment."},{"time":708714,"text":"Here, as we make a lane change,\nthe car to our left decides"},{"time":711565,"text":"it wants to as well."},{"time":715118,"text":"And here, we watch a car\nblow through a red light"},{"time":717811,"text":"and yield to it."},{"time":719901,"text":"And similarly, here, a cyclist\nblowing through that light as well."},{"time":723755,"text":"And of course,\nthe vehicle responds safely."},{"time":726501,"text":"And of course, we have people\nwho do I don't know what"},{"time":729102,"text":"sometimes on the road, like this guy\npulling out between two self-driving cars."},{"time":732925,"text":"You have to ask, \"What are you thinking?\""},{"time":734970,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":736182,"text":"Now, I just fire-hosed you\nwith a lot of stuff there,"},{"time":738703,"text":"so I'm going to break one of these\ndown pretty quickly."},{"time":741353,"text":"So what we're looking at is the scene\nwith the cyclist again,"},{"time":744293,"text":"and you might notice in the bottom,\nwe can't actually see the cyclist yet,"},{"time":747784,"text":"but the car can: it's that little\nblue box up there,"},{"time":750288,"text":"and that comes from the laser data."},{"time":752369,"text":"And that's not actually\nreally easy to understand,"},{"time":754787,"text":"so what I'm going to do is I'm going\nto turn that laser data and look at it,"},{"time":758371,"text":"and if you're really good at looking\nat laser data, you can see"},{"time":761400,"text":"a few dots on the curve there,"},{"time":762887,"text":"right there, and that blue box\nis that cyclist."},{"time":765259,"text":"Now as our light is red,"},{"time":766408,"text":"the cyclist's light\nhas turned yellow already,"},{"time":768600,"text":"and if you squint, you can see that\nin the imagery."},{"time":771038,"text":"But the cyclist, we see, is going\nto proceed through the intersection."},{"time":774324,"text":"Our light has now turned green,\nhis is solidly red,"},{"time":776718,"text":"and we now anticipate that this bike\nis going to come all the way across."},{"time":781010,"text":"Unfortunately the other drivers next to us\nwere not paying as much attention."},{"time":784752,"text":"They started to pull forward,\nand fortunately for everyone,"},{"time":787909,"text":"this cyclists reacts, avoids,"},{"time":790920,"text":"and makes it through the intersection."},{"time":793111,"text":"And off we go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":794679,"text":"Now, as you can see, we've made\nsome pretty exciting progress,"},{"time":797627,"text":"and at this point we're pretty convinced"},{"time":799529,"text":"this technology is going\nto come to market."},{"time":801539,"text":"We do three million miles of testing\nin our simulators every single day,"},{"time":806322,"text":"so you can imagine the experience\nthat our vehicles have."},{"time":809011,"text":"We are looking forward to having\nthis technology on the road,"},{"time":811875,"text":"and we think the right path\nis to go through the self-driving"},{"time":814765,"text":"rather than driver assistance approach"},{"time":816609,"text":"because the urgency is so large."},{"time":819230,"text":"In the time I have given this talk today,"},{"time":821623,"text":"34 people have died on America's roads."}]},{"cues":[{"time":824758,"text":"How soon can we bring it out?"},{"time":827126,"text":"Well, it's hard to say because\nit's a really complicated problem,"},{"time":830958,"text":"but these are my two boys."},{"time":833172,"text":"My oldest son is 11, and that means\nin four and a half years,"},{"time":836795,"text":"he's going to be able\nto get his driver's license."},{"time":839372,"text":"My team and I are committed\nto making sure that doesn't happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":842576,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844480,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":849110,"text":"Chris Anderson: Chris,\nI've got a question for you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":851678,"text":"Chris Urmson: Sure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":854487,"text":"CA: So certainly, the mind of your cars\nis pretty mind-boggling."},{"time":858411,"text":"On this debate between\ndriver-assisted and fully driverless --"},{"time":862870,"text":"I mean, there's a real debate\ngoing on out there right now."},{"time":865911,"text":"So some of the companies,\nfor example, Tesla,"},{"time":868744,"text":"are going the driver-assisted route."},{"time":870903,"text":"What you're saying is that\nthat's kind of going to be a dead end"},{"time":876151,"text":"because you can't just keep improving\nthat route and get to fully driverless"},{"time":881607,"text":"at some point, and then a driver\nis going to say, \"This feels safe,\""},{"time":885137,"text":"and climb into the back,\nand something ugly will happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":887784,"text":"CU: Right. No, that's exactly right,\nand it's not to say"},{"time":890460,"text":"that the driver assistance systems\naren't going to be incredibly valuable."},{"time":893997,"text":"They can save a lot of lives\nin the interim,"},{"time":896055,"text":"but to see the transformative opportunity\nto help someone like Steve get around,"},{"time":899888,"text":"to really get to the end case in safety,"},{"time":901857,"text":"to have the opportunity\nto change our cities"},{"time":904336,"text":"and move parking out and get rid of\nthese urban craters we call parking lots,"},{"time":908540,"text":"it's the only way to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":909780,"text":"CA: We will be tracking your progress\nwith huge interest."},{"time":912498,"text":"Thanks so much, Chris.\nCU: Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}